A fire outbreak has been reported at the Presidential Villa in Aso Rock, Abuja, causing confusion among workers in President Muhammadu Buhari's abode. SaharaReporters learnt that the fire started at 4 pm as the fire service officials tried desperately to put it out. SaharaReporters Media "The security men were chasing people not to capture the incident, but I tried my best to capture it. The fire is still on," a source told SaharaReporters around 9 pm.  FLASH: Fire Breaks Out In Aso Villa@NGRPresident @NigeriaGov pic.twitter.com/8EdfYGudbq  Although the cause of the fire is not yet known, fire service trucks have moved in and were seen in the villa.